. We do find one example of a peripheral\nstar-forming site that appears only in the feedback run, thus having a\ntriggered origin. However, this appears to be the exception rather than the\nrule, although this may be an artifact of our simplified radiative transfer\nscheme.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 28 Mar 2020 05:11:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 24 Sep 2020 01:33:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-09-25"}
