ely well with the GC when assuming a blue\nhorizontal branch (BHB) nature for it. HVS$\\,$22 is by far the most extreme\nobject in the sample. Although its origin is completely unconstrained, an\nejection from the GC by the Hills mechanism is the most plausible explanation\nfor its current Galactic rest-frame velocity of\n$1530^{+690}_{-560}\\,$km$\\,$s${}^{-1}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 28 Mar 2020 10:55:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-05-13"}
